text.tspan: Death rate from communicable vs. non-communicable diseases, 2021
The estimated annual death rate per 100,000 people. Death rates are compared between non-communicable
diseases, versus infectious, maternal, neonatal and nutritional diseases combined.
Infections, maternal, neonatal and nutritional diseases
Data source: IHME, Global Burden of Disease (2024); Our World In Data
Note: To allow for comparisons between countries and over time, this metric is age-standardized.
